# Clawkie-Talkie client env template.
#
# Copy to `client/.env.local` and edit. Vite loads these at dev/build
# time; only variables prefixed `VITE_` are exposed to browser code.
#
# No variables are currently required. The phone client reaches the
# daemon's PeerJS signaling via same-origin `/peerjs` — Vite proxies it
# to the in-process PeerServer in dev, and the host (e.g. jump.sh)
# forwards it in deployments. The daemon registers under a deterministic
# peer ID (`ct-daemon`); the base URL is enough to dial in.
